Art Toronto, previously known as the Toronto International Art Fair, is an international contemporary art exhibition held each year in Toronto, Ontario, Canada at the Metro Toronto Convention Centre. The first exhibition was held in 2000 (2000) and the most recent in October 2017. Since its inception, it has grown to become the pre-eminent forum for displaying contemporary art in Canada, with exhibitors from around the world.
The Fair has a series of Special Projects that contribute to a dialogue on contemporary art.
